          "source": "adjusted",
          "ins_item_num": 8,
          "ins_total": 1659.05,
          "f9": "Our line item covers insurance line 8.\n\nWe are requesting 45.0 SQ of Roofing Felt - 15 lb. The insurance report shows 40.2 SQ; we are using the EagleView suggested square footage of 45.0 SQ which includes the appropriate waste factor.\n\n1. The difference is $196.29. Per Xactimate pricing, the cost is $1,825.65. While the insurance report shows $1,659.05.\n\na. Roofing felt, like shingles, must be installed in a staggered and overlapping pattern to ensure proper water shedding and code compliance. During this process, cuts are required at eaves, valleys, hips, ridges, and roof penetrations, which inevitably generates material waste. This waste is a necessary part of achieving a watertight underlayment system. Applying a waste percentage to roofing felt is both customary and essential to complete the work properly and bring the property back to its pre-loss condition.\n\nb. Please see attached EagleView showing the waste calculation for the shingles. It also shows the exact squares for the felt.\n\nc. Currently the insurance is paying for 40.2 SQ while we are requesting 45.0 SQ which is an additional 4.8 SQ.",
          "photo_anchor": "roofing-felt",
          "sub_name": ""
        },
